def: An actuality; a conception completely actualized, indistinction from mere potential existence.
One who testifies; one who gives testimony, or bears witness toprove anything; a witness.

The Vulgate rendering of the Hebrew word qipod, which in the"Authorized Version" is translated bittern, and in the RevisedVersion, porcupine.I will make it [Babylon] a possession for the ericius and pools ofwaters. Is. xiv. 23 (Douay version).
The protection of the interior walls of a fortification from anenfilading fire, as by covering them, or by a high parapet on theexposed side.
A lynx. See 1st Lucern and Loup-cervier.
The act of drawing apart; separation.
Defensive armor used for the whole body and often for thehorse, also, esp. the linked mail or scale armor of some easternnations.
Righteous in one's own esteem; pharisaic.
A collection of blood, pus, or other fluid, in some cavity ofthe body, especially that of the pleura. Dunglison.
